{
  "stem": "4289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he took me outside and there was my mother and he gave us back our luggage and yelled at as.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He said, don't think that somebody else will be as nice as I am.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Don't  you do that ever again because next time when we find you, this is not going to be the end.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You're going to be punished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But we still did the same thing, I remember.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Towards almost the end of the war, we were selling merchandise on trains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was probably between my age four and six.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For two years, we were schlepping on those trains, day and night and staying with strangers, sleeping over, I don't know, probably people that she knew from before.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or just people on the train, she would ask where can we sleep over, and we slept with strange people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Grandma.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Grandma did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Grandpa and grandma did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Grandpa, I don't think so, but grandma, for sure.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did it for the longest time, till the end of the war, probably 1944 or '45.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Overnight, we saw the change because German soldiers and Gestapo, overnight they disappeared from our town.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And children were running around barefoot and running through the offices of the Germans, and picking up whatever there was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were rumors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Let's go here.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Let's go there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There is sugar.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There is, you know, chocolate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There is whatever.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I ran with a horde of children, barefoot, whatever, because I was always barefoot and schlepping my sister with me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was her defender, and I was carrying her in my hands.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was the end.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember also that the tanks came into the town, and people were really celebrating, and drinking, and singing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the soldiers were very happy, picking up children, and kissing them.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
